===Climate===
Lucknow has a warm [[humid subtropical climate]] with cool, dry winters from December to February and dry, hot summers from April to June. The rainy season is from mid-June to mid-September, when Lucknow gets an average rainfall of {{convert|896.2|mm|in}} from the south-west [[monsoon]] winds, and occasionally frontal rainfall will occur in January. In winter the maximum temperature is around {{convert|25|C|F|0}} and the minimum is in the 2 to 3 degrees Celsius range. Fog is quite common from late December to late January. Summers are extremely hot with temperatures rising to the 40 to 45 degree Celsius range, the average highs being in the high 30s.
